The paper presents a framework for privacy-preserving releasing of complex data using deep generative models. This involves techniques from machine learning (deep learning, generative models) and privacy (differential privacy). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper deals with privacy. The paper also involves data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) as it deals with releasing data. Finally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses deep generative models.
